HEADWORD: graviton
<hw>graviton</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A theoretical
gauge boson that mediates the (extremely weak) gravitational
interactions between particles; the quantum of the gravitational field,
having zero rest mass and a spin of 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

